SBADescriptor.Name: Analyze Logon Duration
SBADescriptor.Description:
Get a detailed overview of the most recent logon process for a specific user. This SBA queries the event log for every major event that relates to the logon process. Use this SBA to track down which phase is responsible for delays during the logon process.
For XenDesktop/XenApp sessions, provide a user with admin rights to the Citrix Site in either a UPN or "Down-Level Logon Name" format. For example: "CitrixAdmin@Domain" or "Domain\CitrixAdmin".
This script requires that ‘Process Creation’ and 'Process Termination' security auditing are enabled
It is recommended that the ‘Security’ log size will be increased to at least 50MB.
